def: Border; margin; edge; verge. [Poetic] Tennyson.Along the river's stony marge. Wordsworth.
A small branch of a root; a rootlet.

To divest or deprive of national character or rights.Bonaparte's decree denationalizes, as he calls it, all ships thathave touched at a British port. Cobbett.An expatriated, denationalized race. G. Eliot.
The examination or study of the soft palate, posterior nares,etc., by means of a laryngoscopic mirror introduced into the pharynx.
Being about the middle of the ordinary age of man; between 30and 50 years old.
One who traffic illegaly; a smuggler.
A white heat, or the glowing or luminous whiteness of a bodycaused by intense heat.
Retired; secluded. "Sequestered scenes." Cowper.Along the cool, sequestered vale of life. Gray.
